CommandText:
DEFINE
    ---- MODEL MEASURES BEGIN ----
    MEASURE Sales[L1] =
        SWITCH (
            SELECTEDVALUE ( 'Product'[Brand] ),
            "Adventure Works", [L1 - Adventure Works],
            "Contoso", [L1 - Contoso],
            "Fabrikam", [L1 - Fabrikam] * .9,
            "Litware", [L1 - Litware] * .95,
            [Sales Amount]
        )
    MEASURE Sales[L1 - Adventure Works] =
        CALCULATE (
            [Sales Amount] * .7,
            KEEPFILTERS ( 'Product'[Brand] = "Adventure Works" )
        )
    MEASURE Sales[L1 - Contoso] =
        CALCULATE ( [Sales Amount] * .8, KEEPFILTERS ( 'Product'[Brand] = "Contoso" ) )
    MEASURE Sales[L1 - Fabrikam] =
        CALCULATE ( [Sales Amount] * .9, KEEPFILTERS ( 'Product'[Brand] = "Fabrikam" ) )
    MEASURE Sales[L1 - Litware] =
        CALCULATE ( [Sales Amount] * .95, KEEPFILTERS ( 'Product'[Brand] = "Litware" ) )
    MEASURE Sales[L2] =
        SUMX ( VALUES ( 'Product'[Brand] ), [L1] )
    MEASURE Sales[L3] =
        SWITCH (
            SELECTEDVALUE ( 'Date'[Year] ),
            2021, [L3 - 2021],
            2022, [L3 - 2022],
            2023, [L3 - 2023],
            2024, [L3 - 2024],
            [L2]
        )
    MEASURE Sales[L3 - 2021] =
        CALCULATE ( [Sales Amount] * 1.01, KEEPFILTERS ( 'Date'[Year] = 2021 ) )
    MEASURE Sales[L3 - 2022] =
        CALCULATE ( [Sales Amount] * 1.03, KEEPFILTERS ( 'Date'[Year] = 2022 ) )
    MEASURE Sales[L3 - 2023] =
        CALCULATE ( [Sales Amount] * 1.06, KEEPFILTERS ( 'Date'[Year] = 2023 ) )
    MEASURE Sales[L3 - 2024] =
        CALCULATE ( [Sales Amount] * 1.07, KEEPFILTERS ( 'Date'[Year] = 2024 ) )
    MEASURE Sales[L4] =
        SUMX ( VALUES ( 'Date'[Year] ), [L3] )


    -- This is the measure optimized using functions
//    MEASURE Sales[L4 Functions] =
//        SUMX (
//            SUMMARIZECOLUMNS ( 'Product'[Brand], 'Date'[Year], "@Sales", [Sales Amount] ),
//            BrandFactor ( YearFactor ( [@Sales], 'Date'[Year] ), 'Product'[Brand] )
//        )
        
        
    -- This is the measure optimized without using functions:
    -- the logic for BrandFactor and YearFactor must be included in the iterator
    MEASURE Sales[L4 Optimized] =
        SUMX (
            SUMMARIZECOLUMNS ( 'Product'[Brand], 'Date'[Year], "@Sales", [Sales Amount] ),
            VAR YearFactor =
                SWITCH ( 'Date'[Year], 2021, 1.01, 2022, 1.03, 2023, 1.06, 2024, 1.07, 1 )
            VAR BrandFactor =
                SWITCH (
                    'Product'[Brand],
                    "Adventure Works", .7,
                    "Contoso", .8,
                    "Fabrikam", .9,
                    "Litware", .95,
                    1
                )
            VAR Result = [@Sales] * YearFactor * BrandFactor
            RETURN
                Result
        )
    ---- MODEL MEASURES END ----
    VAR __DS0Core =
        SUMMARIZECOLUMNS (
            ROLLUPADDISSUBTOTAL ( 'Product'[Brand], "IsGrandTotalRowTotal" ),
            "L4", 'Sales'[L4 Optimized]
        )
    VAR __DS0PrimaryWindowed =
        TOPN ( 502, __DS0Core, [IsGrandTotalRowTotal], 0, 'Product'[Brand], 1 )

EVALUATE
__DS0PrimaryWindowed
ORDER BY
    [IsGrandTotalRowTotal] DESC,
    'Product'[Brand]
